Commentary: around the wicket comes Ndlovu, and Gurbaz is immediately off the mark, clipping a single off his toes
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, 1 run

Commentary: darted in flat and fast by Ndlovu, and it's blocked back at him
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: low arm this time, and some drift across the left-hander, who tucks a single to cover
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Hazratullah Zazai, 1 run

Commentary: big swing and a miss! The ball zips past the batsman, and the keeper too, and they run some byes. Madziva is after it, and he falls awkwardly as he dives to stop the ball near third man. His knee plugs in the turf, and he's grimacing ... but he's eventually up, and fine
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, 2 byes

Commentary: slanting in to him with the arm, and a single is glanced to fine leg
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, 1 run

Commentary: the bottom hand does the work, Hazratullah glancing wide of midwicket and calling early for a second
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Hazratullah Zazai, 2 runs

Commentary: and he starts with a peach of a delivery! On a length, pulling him forward, and then shaping away from the right hander to beat the outside edge
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: this one hits the seam and nips back in, Gurbaz staying deep in the crease and poking to cover
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: thick inside edge, Gurbaz thrusting his hands out at a length delivery that seams back in. Short fine leg cleans up
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: slower ball, lifted over mid off! Floated up harmlessly outside off by Jarvis, and he just swings his hands through the line. Doesn't bother keeping it down either
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, FOUR runs

Commentary: and now a pull, a short ball sitting up on a leg stump line. It's met with a muscly pull to deep backward square
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, FOUR runs

Commentary: pulled again, but this one is off the splice and in the air. It goes well in front of square and plugs in the outfield. And they're back for a third as the fielder is slow getting to it. I think it's Madziva, who hurt his knee in the first over. Jarvis suggests he should go off the field if he can't run
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, 3 runs

Commentary: outswinger to start, on a length just outside off. He's forward to defend to cover
Commentary_short: Chatara to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: a touch straighter, and slightly shorter. Gurbaz fends to leg and they pinch a single
Commentary_short: Chatara to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, 1 run

Commentary: is this a drop? Chatara pitches one up, and Zazai hammers it very hard back at him. He gets his hands down, but can't cling on. It was fiercely hit
Commentary_short: Chatara to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: straight, and shaping in to Zazai's pads. He likes to attack the leg side, but this one is softly dinked away for a single
Commentary_short: Chatara to Hazratullah Zazai, 1 run

Commentary: chipped over mid on! This got more height than distance, but Williams running back from mid on couldn't quite get there in time
Commentary_short: Chatara to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, 2 runs

Commentary: picked up handsomely! Rahmanullah's trigger movement is back and well across to the off side. That puts him in the perfect position to pick this hit-me delivery up over fine leg. The line wasn't great, headed down the leg side, but he made the most of it with a fantastic strike. First six of the innings
Commentary_short: Chatara to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, SIX runs

Commentary: rising off a length, and straight. Zazai's got no room to work with, and nudges softly to leg
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: slower ball, an offcutter. Zazai reads it and angles a single just wide of short third man
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Hazratullah Zazai, 1 run

Commentary: he gets inside the line, and scoops over fine leg!. Rahmanullah manufactures the line he wants by getting right across to the off side, and purposefully lifts this one over the man at short fine
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, FOUR runs

Commentary: thump! Jarvis' riposte is a nippy bouncer, and Gurbaz takes his eyes off it as he pulls, and is hit on the back of the helmet. He doesn't have neck guards back there, but it's hit him on the rim of the helmet
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: edged to third man, off a booming drive. The next ball is pitched up, and he flings everything at it, a thick edge flying fast to the boundary
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, FOUR runs

Commentary: skewed down to third man, once again it's not the shot he was trying to play. Gurbaz was eyeing the leg side, but the ball flashed off a thick edge, over short third man, and down to the boundary
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, FOUR runs

Commentary: and Zazai welcomes him with a huge mow! Looped up on middle and leg, and he bends down to spank it over midwicket
Commentary_short: Williams to Hazratullah Zazai, SIX runs

Commentary: but he misses this one. Zazai aims to repeat the treatment, but this time the ball spins past the shot and hits his shoulder
Commentary_short: Williams to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: quicker, flatter, and it's pushed back at him
Commentary_short: Williams to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: some grip and spin for Williams, the ball landing full and spinning in to strike Zazai on the pad. Headed down leg
Commentary_short: Williams to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: flicked off the pads, and through square leg for one
Commentary_short: Williams to Hazratullah Zazai, 1 run

Commentary: speared down the leg side, Taylor jumping across to stop it
Commentary_short: Williams to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, 1 wide

Commentary: well bowled, landing on off stump and spinning away to keep him honest
Commentary_short: Williams to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: Zazai steps half forward to push an offcutter just wide of cover, running a quick single to bring up the fifty
Commentary_short: Chatara to Hazratullah Zazai, 1 run

Commentary: pulled over fine leg! Gurbaz is toying with Zimbabwe's bowlers, and once again he steps across to the off side to turn a straight delivery into a leg-side one, pulling the ball deliberately up and over fine leg. And it goes all the way
Commentary_short: Chatara to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, SIX runs

Commentary: this time he stays put, and dabs a wide back-of-a-length delivery down to third man
Commentary_short: Chatara to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, 1 run

Commentary: sliced, skied, and caught! Zazai, who has been somewhat overshadowed by Gurbaz, targets a big hit over the leg side. But the ball is angled across him, and it flies off the outside half of the blade, looping up to be easily caught by Williams in the covers. Some relief for Zimbabwe after a rapid opening stand
Commentary_short: Chatara to Hazratullah Zazai, OUT
Dismissal_text: Hazratullah Zazai c Williams b Chatara 13 (14b 0x4 1x6) SR: 92.85

Commentary: nipping in off the seam, landing on a length, Gurbaz defending to cover
Commentary_short: Chatara to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: fuller this time, and he taps towards point and sets off. Ndlovu fires a throw at the non-striker's end, but it's slightly off target and they scamper through
Commentary_short: Chatara to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, 1 run

Commentary: this one scuttles through a little low, Gurbaz whipping across his front pad to find a single to midwicket
Commentary_short: Williams to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, 1 run

Commentary: appeal for a stumping! Williams gives this one a real rip, and it dips and spins past Tarakai as he stretches forward to defend. Taylor is lightning behind the stumps, and it seems as though his back foot was raised for a just a moment. But has he got it down in time? Good grief, this is mighty close. The tv umpire eventually has to make a call, and decides it's not out. That was a tough decision to make!
Commentary_short: Williams to Najeeb Tarakai, no run

Commentary: spinning away from him outside off, and it's cut to backward point
Commentary_short: Williams to Najeeb Tarakai, no run

Commentary: pushed to cover now, and Tarakai wants a single. There's none to be had, and he's wisely sent back
Commentary_short: Williams to Najeeb Tarakai, no run

Commentary: nicely bowled once more, but Tarakai finds the right angle to push down to long off, beating short extra
Commentary_short: Williams to Najeeb Tarakai, 1 run

Commentary: huge appeal, and he's given! After an over of flighted deliveries, Williams fires in a quicker one that rushes on with the arm, beating the sweep and striking him flush on the pad. The umpire upholds the lbw appeal, but Gurbaz queries it with a review. The ball's pretty close to the gloves as it goes through, and once again Masudur Rahman the television umpire has a very difficult decision to make. UltraEdge seems to indicate there is no bat involved, and ball tracking confirms the umpire's call!
Commentary_short: Williams to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, OUT
Dismissal_text: Rahmanullah Gurbaz lbw b Williams 43 (24b 5x4 2x6) SR: 179.16

Commentary: and immediately there's another appeal for a stumping. This is a much easier call though. Taylor is once again very slick getting the bails off, but his back foot is definitely grounded behind the line
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Najeeb Tarakai, no run

Commentary: cracking delivery! Ndlovu rips one outside off, beating a groping defensive push
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Najeeb Tarakai, no run

Commentary: top edge, but it falls safe! It was the quicker one, and it rushed on to him as he tried to pull. The ball goes up, towards long on, but doesn't have the legs to reach him
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Najeeb Tarakai, 1 run

Commentary: whipped off the toes, into the leg side
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Asghar Afghan, 1 run

Commentary: biffed over long on! Slightly too full from Ndlovu, and Tarakai's eyes light up. A big swing of the blade sends the ball flying over long on
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Najeeb Tarakai, SIX runs

Commentary: good comeback, hitting the right length and getting some purchase to hurry a push back at him
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Najeeb Tarakai, no run

Commentary: dip, grip and spin! This one rags across his defensive push. Masakadza offers encouragement from slip
Commentary_short: Williams to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: beaten outside off! Plenty of spin here
Commentary_short: Williams to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: fuller, straighter, and it's driven back past a diving bowler
Commentary_short: Williams to Asghar Afghan, 1 run

Commentary: worked off the pads once again, and there's room for another quick single
Commentary_short: Williams to Najeeb Tarakai, 1 run

Commentary: pushed just wide of cover, and there's some indecision in the running. Eventually they decide to take the run, and make it to the other side
Commentary_short: Williams to Asghar Afghan, 1 run

Commentary: beaten! This was there to be hit, to be honest, as Williams digs it in much too short. But the ball just zips on, beating Tarakai's attempted pull
Commentary_short: Williams to Najeeb Tarakai, no run

Commentary: legbreak, spinning away from him, and he taps to backward point
Commentary_short: Burl to Asghar Afghan, 1 run

Commentary: big sweep, but it comes off the toe end and trickles to midwicket
Commentary_short: Burl to Najeeb Tarakai, 1 run

Commentary: was this the googly? It slid straight on in to him, cramping Asghar's push to cover
Commentary_short: Burl to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: too straight, and it's flicked off the pads
Commentary_short: Burl to Asghar Afghan, 1 run

Commentary: big slog sweep, but the ball spins past him and he hits only fresh air
Commentary_short: Burl to Najeeb Tarakai, no run

Commentary: down the track this time, and he's almost beaten in the flight but manages a drive to long off
Commentary_short: Burl to Najeeb Tarakai, 1 run

Commentary: length ball on the stumps, punched off the back foot towards mid-on
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Najeeb Tarakai, 1 run

Commentary: down the ground and absolutely smashed, but straight towards the bowler
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: fuller and slower around off, turns it towards midwicket
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Asghar Afghan, 1 run

Commentary: fuller on the stumps, looks to slog it down the ground, mistimes it towards the right of long-on
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Najeeb Tarakai, 1 run

Commentary: short around off, sits up for the batsman but Afghan can pull it only towards deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Asghar Afghan, 1 run

Commentary: a bit of a mix-up but all safe in the end. Was a length ball outside off, Tarakai punched it towards covers and set off, Asghar was a bit late to react and there was almost a collision between the two batsman but Asghar makes it comfortably in the end
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Najeeb Tarakai, 1 run

Commentary: tossed up outside off and spinning away, goes for the cut but cannot middle, backward point comes into the picture
Commentary_short: Williams to Najeeb Tarakai, no run

Commentary: stops at the batsman who was shaping up for a cut, ends up hitting it in the air towards extra cover where Ndlovu makes no mistake, moving to his left
Commentary_short: Williams to Najeeb Tarakai, OUT
Dismissal_text: Najeeb Tarakai c Ndlovu b Williams 14 (19b 0x4 1x6) SR: 73.68

Commentary: length ball outside off, flight and turn, defended from the front foot
Commentary_short: Williams to Najibullah Zadran, no run

Commentary: goes for the reverse sweep but Williams has once again bowled it slower through the air, some turn as well to beat the batsman and hit on the body
Commentary_short: Williams to Najibullah Zadran, no run

Commentary: length but down the leg side and spinning further away
Commentary_short: Williams to Najibullah Zadran, 1 wide

Commentary: length ball on the stumps, flicks it away but finds square leg
Commentary_short: Williams to Najibullah Zadran, no run

Commentary: length ball on the pads, glanced fine this time to beat the short fine leg and collect a couple
Commentary_short: Williams to Najibullah Zadran, 2 runs

Commentary: short and wide outside off, Afghan goes for the cut but mistimes it into the ground
Commentary_short: Madziva to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: a slower bouncer outside off, Afghan was early into the pull and gets beaten
Commentary_short: Madziva to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: another slower one, closer to the batsman this time and Afghan swivels to pull it towards deep square leg
Commentary_short: Madziva to Asghar Afghan, 1 run

Commentary: length ball in the line of the stumps, keeps a bit low as well, Najibullah goes for the flick and gets beaten, a loud appeal for lbw but not out. Pitched way outside the leg stump
Commentary_short: Madziva to Najibullah Zadran, no run

Commentary: another slower one, short outside off, Najibullah looks to pull but is beaten
Commentary_short: Madziva to Najibullah Zadran, no run

Commentary: and again, another slower one angling across the batsman who was early into the pull, no connection
Commentary_short: Madziva to Najibullah Zadran, no run

Commentary: down the ground  and lofted over deep midwicket, was a six as soon as it made that sweet contact with the bat
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Asghar Afghan, SIX runs

Commentary: fuller on the stumps and Asghar once again looks to repeat the shot. However, he only gets the height on this one, not the distance. Ryan Burl settles under it at long-on and pouches it as it comes down after ages
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Asghar Afghan, OUT
Dismissal_text: Asghar Afghan c Burl b Ndlovu 14 (16b 0x4 1x6) SR: 87.50

Commentary: short and flat on the stumps, Najibullah rocks back and smashes it over deep midwicket for the second six of the over
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Najibullah Zadran, SIX runs

Commentary: flatter and quicker, angling away from the batsman, Najibullah goes for the cut, gets a thick outside edge that beats short third man
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Najibullah Zadran, FOUR runs

Commentary: length ball on the pads, turns it behind square leg, was looking to come back for the second but only one was available there
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run

Commentary: length ball around off, defended tentatively from the crease
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Mohammad Nabi, no run

Commentary: short again, angling across, Najibullah was looking to ramp it over but it's a touch too wide
Commentary_short: Madziva to Najibullah Zadran, no run

Commentary: another slower one, this time on a length on the leg stump, Najibullah defends it on the off side and scampers across
Commentary_short: Madziva to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run

Commentary: short and wide outside off, punched firmly off the back foot, sweeper cover cuts it off
Commentary_short: Madziva to Mohammad Nabi, 1 run

Commentary: short outside off, cuts it towards deep point for one
Commentary_short: Madziva to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run

Commentary: another slower bouncer but down the leg side this time, the umpires signals a no-ball as it's the second bouncer of the over
Commentary_short: Madziva to Mohammad Nabi, 1 no ball

Commentary: slower length ball, Nabi can only drag it towards deep midwicket, comes back for the second though
Commentary_short: Madziva to Mohammad Nabi, 2 runs

Commentary: slower again, fuller outside off this time, Nabi just places it between midwicket and square leg and sneaks in another brace
Commentary_short: Madziva to Mohammad Nabi, 2 runs

Commentary: short of length aimed at the batsman, cramping for room, tucked away towards midwicket for one
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run

Commentary: fuller around off, Nabi backs away and digs it out towards long-on
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Mohammad Nabi, 1 run

Commentary: short of length at the batsman, Najib stays back and tucks it away towards fine leg
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run

Commentary: short again, just around off, Nabi pulls it towards deep-backward square leg, fielder there
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Mohammad Nabi, 1 run

Commentary: another short ball, looked like a slower one, but this time Najib manages to pull it fine, between the keeper and the man at 45 and collects a much-needed boundary
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Najibullah Zadran, FOUR runs

Commentary: over long-on this time. Was in the slot, Najib cleared his front leg, and lofted it high and handsome to clear to boundary. 14 from that Jarvis over
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Najibullah Zadran, SIX runs

Commentary: fuller on the stumps, and Nabi drills it straight back, hits the stumps at the other end, a single off the ricochet
Commentary_short: Chatara to Mohammad Nabi, 1 run

Commentary: in the blockhole around off, looks to smash it through covers, loses shape and the ball rolls behind square leg off the inner half
Commentary_short: Chatara to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run

Commentary: legcutter from Chatara but too short and Nabi just waits at the back foot before pulling it way over the deep midwicket boundary
Commentary_short: Chatara to Mohammad Nabi, SIX runs

Commentary: fuller, doesn't miss the yorker by much but Nabi clears the front leg and makes full use of the bottom hand it smash it for a straight six
Commentary_short: Chatara to Mohammad Nabi, SIX runs

Commentary: three in three for Nabi! A low full toss on the stumps, Nabi was just standing very still in his crease and sends it over deep midwicket. Moves to 26 off 11
Commentary_short: Chatara to Mohammad Nabi, SIX runs

Commentary: is that the fourth one? Yes!!! Another low full toss from Chatara, this time outside off and Nabi moves towards the off stump and lofts it over deep extra cover. Another big over for Afghanistan - 26 from that
Commentary_short: Chatara to Mohammad Nabi, SIX runs

Commentary: Madziva too disappears! Was a length ball and Najib just pulls it with utter disdain, over deep midwicket, that's fifth six in last five balls
Commentary_short: Madziva to Najibullah Zadran, SIX runs

Commentary: makes it six in six! Short, just outside off and pulled almost into the second tier this time, way over deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Madziva to Najibullah Zadran, SIX runs

Commentary: this is carnage! A slower one gone wrong, loopy delivery down the leg side, Najib helps it over fine leg. Another six. Seven now. This must be some kind of a record
Commentary_short: Madziva to Najibullah Zadran, SIX runs

Commentary: a full toss but way too outside off, called wide
Commentary_short: Madziva to Najibullah Zadran, 1 wide

Commentary: fuller and wider and carved over point, is that another six? They are checking upstairs but looks like it landed just inside. That's fifty for Najibullah, off just 22 balls
Commentary_short: Madziva to Najibullah Zadran, FOUR runs

Commentary: fuller outside off, steered towards sweeper cover for one
Commentary_short: Madziva to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run

Commentary: short again, Nabi goes for the pull but cannot beat the man at deep-backward square leg
Commentary_short: Madziva to Mohammad Nabi, 1 run

Commentary: a low full toss on the stumps, whipped away towards deep midwicket but only a single
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Mohammad Nabi, 1 run

Commentary: fuller outside off, digs it out towards deep extra cover
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run

Commentary: in the blockhole and Nabi brings out that bottom hand but only a single this time, to long-on
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Mohammad Nabi, 1 run

Commentary: in the blockhole but just outside off, Najibullah squeezes it out past short third man for four
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Najibullah Zadran, FOUR runs

Commentary: goes for the yorker but just misses, Najibullah lofts it towards long-off, a bit of fumble there allows the second run
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Najibullah Zadran, 2 runs

Commentary: wide, low full toss and Najibullah makes full use of that, dispatches it over deep extra cover, fifth six of the innings for him
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Najibullah Zadran, SIX runs

Commentary: another full toss on the stumps, swiped towards deep midwicket for a couple, the throw is in but Najib was dragging hi bat, they are checking upstairs and Najib was well in
Commentary_short: Chatara to Mohammad Nabi, 2 runs

Commentary: another yorker gone wrong. Nabi smashes it over the bowler's head. Madzavi sprints from long-off, dives to his right and makes the stop
Commentary_short: Chatara to Mohammad Nabi, 1 run

Commentary: fuller outside off, in the blockhole. Finally they get one right. Najib mistimes it back towards the bowler
Commentary_short: Chatara to Najibullah Zadran, no run

Commentary: another full toss, wide outside off, Najib goes aerial over extra cover, didn't middle it but it still runs away for four before the long-off fielder could reach there
Commentary_short: Chatara to Najibullah Zadran, FOUR runs

Commentary: a wide yorker this time, squeezes it out towards extra cover
Commentary_short: Chatara to Najibullah Zadran, 1 run

Commentary: in the blockhole, almost a yorker at the leg stump, Nabi was deep in his crease, lofts it towards long-on with that big bottom hand but doesn't get enough to clear Burl who times his hop and takes it
Commentary_short: Chatara to Mohammad Nabi, OUT
Dismissal_text: Mohammad Nabi c Burl b Chatara 38 (18b 0x4 4x6) SR: 211.11

Commentary: Taylor attempts a reverse sweep, but misses the shot and is struck on the pad. Outside the line I should think, but they ask for a review. There's a flat line on UltraEdge, but ball-tracking shows he's clearly hit outside the line. A wasted review.
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, no run

Commentary: misdirected down the leg side, and Taylor meets this one with a powerful orthodox sweep, placing it to perfection to collect a boundary
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, FOUR runs

Commentary: pushed through a little quicker, Taylor whips across his pad to midwicket
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, no run

Commentary: tucked just wide of mid on, but they decide against a single
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, no run

Commentary: slog sweep, four more! He didn't get all of this one, but made sure to hit it well in front of square, and right into the gap
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, FOUR runs

Commentary: quicker one, rushing in to him off the track, and it's inside-edged onto the thigh pad. Gurbaz keeps him in the crease with an energetic dive across from behind the stumps
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, no run

Commentary: he bustles in and delivers a back of a length delivery, the ball shaping slightly in to Masakadza and cramping him for room
Commentary_short: Fareed Ahmad to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: in the air, and safe! He fetches the ball from way outside off stump with an attempted paddle sweep, skying the effort. Fortunately for him, it comes to ground safely, in front of midwicket
Commentary_short: Fareed Ahmad to Masakadza, 1 run

Commentary: shaping in to Taylor off the track, and cramping his attempted push to cover. Tight lines
Commentary_short: Fareed Ahmad to Taylor, no run

Commentary: fine leg is inside the circle, and Taylor looks to beat him, walking across, but he inside edges the effort onto his thigh and pinches a single
Commentary_short: Fareed Ahmad to Taylor, 1 run

Commentary: uppercut over cover point, and they're back for two. Not particularly well timed, but he gets enough on it to clear the inner ring
Commentary_short: Fareed Ahmad to Masakadza, 2 runs

Commentary: this one angles across him, and Masakadza drives hard but straight back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Fareed Ahmad to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: picked up! Mujeeb flings this down the leg side, and Taylor picks it up handsomely over deep backward square. Pinged out of the middle
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, SIX runs

Commentary: straight back over his head! Mujeeb sends down a seam-up delivery, but it's over pitched and Taylor just swings cleanly through the line
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, SIX runs

Commentary: another big heave, this time to leg, and the ball takes the bottom edging, rolling out to the man in the deep
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, 1 run

Commentary: a touch short, and spinning towards leg stump, but Hamilton is rushed on the pull and wears it on the thigh pad
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: run out! Oh dear. Masakadza inside edges a flick to leg and the ball rolls to midwicket. Taylor wants a single and calls immediately, but Hamilton hesitates for a moment before setting off. It's a fatal pause, as the throw comes in flat, hard and accurate to catch him short
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Masakadza, OUT
Dismissal_text: H Masakadza run out (†Rahmanullah Gurbaz) 3 (6b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50.00

Commentary: nudged just to the right of short fine leg, and there's another quick single. Ervine's quick off the mark though, and safely through
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, 1 run

Commentary: thrashed! Fareed offers generous width outside off and Taylor steps forward to flay the ball, in the air but in the gap, through cover point
Commentary_short: Fareed Ahmad to Taylor, FOUR runs

Commentary: past the outside edge, the ball rising off a length to beat a slightly uncertain push off the back foot
Commentary_short: Fareed Ahmad to Taylor, no run

Commentary: angled across him, and close to the off stump. Taylor is half forward to poke to cover
Commentary_short: Fareed Ahmad to Taylor, no run

Commentary: spliced to midwicket, and Hazratullah holds a simple catch. Fine leg was inside the circle, and Taylor was targeting that region. But the ball just got big on him, and he spooned a simple catch in front of square, off the splice. Early joy for Afghanistan, and early strife for Zimbabwe
